author: Desmond Peh
text:
I was promised that this is a vibrant and safe place for gym-goers when I signed up. However, my experience proved it otherwise within a short span of time.

For two consecutive weeks, I was harassed by a member of this particular outlet whom I am totally stranger with. A Terry-ble person who aims to Terry-orise people around him. He is short, plump, slightly bald and speaks in a demanding tone, expecting you to comply as he corrects your posture and use of equipment when he could not even do a proper rep for all his exercises. On every occasion, I brought up this act of harassment to the management but they claimed that they had spoken to him about it. Talk is cheap when there is no improvement at all, this left a very bad taste and it proves to me that it is not safe for me to patronise this outlet anymore.

I was told by the management that the members were loud and this equates to a vibrant environment. There is a huge difference between vibrant and loud, and many gym-goers want a quiet environment to work out.

It is truly disappointing and unsettling. I hope that no one else will go through such an ordeal.

author: twshady
text:
This gym is a great place! Staff are attentive and always open to feedback for improvement.

On a side note, unfortunately, I recently ran into a truly inconsiderate gym user named Desmond Peh. He and his Boyfriend... were lifting light weights but kept slamming them down, then leaving the equipment behind for others to put away for them. Basic courtesy and gym etiquette seemed completely lost on them. If you can‚Äôt handle the weights, don‚Äôt touch them. Go lighter if it's too heavy for you.

So I told this Desmond guy as he did not rack his weights after using them. If this is considered as "harassment" then maybe the coffeeshop aunties are also "harassing" you when they ask you to return your plates. Common sense and basic courtesy shouldn't be that hard.

author: Boom Boom
text:
I wouldn‚Äôt recommend Anytime Fitness to anyone. Joining is effortless, but leaving? That‚Äôs a whole different story. They don‚Äôt let you cancel easily‚Äîyou have to email them after your contract ends, and if anything goes wrong with that email, you‚Äôre forced to keep paying. On top of that, they require a 30-day notice, which is just ridiculous. Why make it so difficult for people to leave?

The gym itself isn‚Äôt worth the stress. It‚Äôs a lot of money per month, yet the service is disappointing. The staff aren‚Äôt helpful, and I‚Äôve seen complaints about rude behaviour. A gym should be welcoming, not frustrating.

If you‚Äôre considering joining, think twice. Getting in is easy, but getting out feels like a trap.

author: Kannina
text: Out of all the AF I've been to, probably the one with the oldest equipment e.g. bumper plates and racks. The racks are so unclean that there's dust bunnies in them. The bumper plates fit very awkwardly on the racks. It just underwent a renovation not long ago but my main gripe is the lack of proper sanitizers. Before the reno at least you had disposable wipes. Now it's just a sad smelly cloth for each level with a spray that looks like it's holding some watered down Dettol. It's definitely not the worst. You can still do your workouts just alright. 2 squat racks, 1 deadlift platform, a bunch of machines, and a spacious functional area on the 2nd floor.

author: Muhammad Zafir
text: The gym facility is excellent, offering a wide range of equipment for all fitness levels. The machines are well-maintained, and there's a great variety of free weights, cardio machines, and functional training areas. The space is clean, well-organized, and never overcrowded, making it easy to get a great workout. Overall, this gym provides a comfortable and motivating environment for anyone looking to improve their fitness.

author: ÈªÑÊñáÂø†
text:
Worst gym experience ever. I went to check out the place before signing up, and the staff barely paid attention to me. They seemed uninterested and acted like they were doing me a favour by answering my questions. That should have been my first red flag.

I still decided to join, thinking maybe the facilities would make up for it. Big mistake. The equipment is always occupied, and some machines are either broken or not well-maintained. The worst part? The cancellation process. It‚Äôs not straightforward at all. You have to email them after your contract ends, and if anything goes wrong, you‚Äôre charged again. Plus, they require one month‚Äôs notice. It just feels like they‚Äôre making it as difficult as possible to leave.

At almost $100 per month, I expected way better. The staff are unprofessional, the gym is overcrowded, and the whole experience is just frustrating. Definitely not worth it.

author: Pei Gen Koh
text: Clean and reliable gym that‚Äôs in a great location for me.

author: Romee TuTu
text:
While registration is easy, cancelling the membership is a nightmare. They require members to send an email after the expiry date, which is unnecessarily troublesome. If they don‚Äôt receive the email (or claim not to), you‚Äôre automatically charged for another month‚Äî$99, no less! They also have a ridiculous 30-day notice period for cancellations. Why make it so hard for members to leave?

For a gym charging this much, the service should at least be decent. Instead, the staff are unprofessional, as seen in other Google reviews where someone was body-shamed. This is unacceptable. If I wanted to donate money, I‚Äôd give it to charity, not to a gym that lacks basic accountability.

Avoid this place unless you enjoy unnecessary fees and poor service.

author: chen rui ying
text:
Not happy with this place at all. Signing up was easy, but cancelling was such a hassle. They said I had to email them after my contract ended, and if they didn‚Äôt get the email, I‚Äôd have to keep paying. On top of that, I had to give one month‚Äôs notice before cancelling. Why make it so hard?

The gym costs $90++ per month, but the service is terrible. The staff are very unprofessional. The way they talk to customers makes me wonder if they have any proper training at all.

Honestly, this place is not worth the money or the trouble.
